# Switch Statement

`switch` is useful when you have many discrete cases.

```dart
switch (variable) {
  case value1:
    // code
    break;
  case value2:
    // code
    break;
  default:
    // code when no match
}
```

- Works with `int`, `String`, or enum types.
- Each case should end with `break` or `continue` (fall-through is allowed with `continue`).
- `default` handles unmatched values.

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  String grade = 'B';
  switch (grade) {
    case 'A':
      print('Excellent!');
      break;
    case 'B':
    case 'C':
      print('Good job!');
      break;
    case 'D':
      print('You passed.');
      break;
    default:
      print('Invalid grade');
  }
}
